   <text>
      <body>
         <div type="letter">
            <pb n="1" facs="Edgeworth_Geneve_33_2_1809_08_22_page01.jpg"/>
            <opener>
               <dateline>
                  <name type="place" ref="./Placeography.xml#Edgeworthstown_IE">Edgeworths town</name>
                  <date when="1809-08-22">August 22, 1809</date></dateline>
               <salute>
                  <persName/>
               </salute>
            </opener>
            <p>My dear Sir, I fear you will be surprised<lb/>
                    by the celerity of our thanks for your letter,<lb/>
                    this moment received, and that you will<lb/>
                    apprehend a tax upon your valuable time<lb/>
                    from such a frequent correspondance -<lb/>
                    But you need not - for I assure you I shall<lb/>
                    not encroach upon your leisure - I know<lb/>
                    its importance - your praise, and your <choice>
                  <orig>cri-<lb/>
                        ticism</orig>
                  <reg>criticism</reg>
               </choice>, and your suggestions, are such as <add>we</add>
               <lb/>
                    canseldom meet with; and could you<lb/>
                    know the delight with which your letters<lb/>
                    are heard by our family circle you would<lb/>
                    not think you have obliged ungrateful<lb/>
                    people <lb/>
            </p>
            <p>I will not mix any literature with<lb/>
                    the business of this my letter - I wrote to you a<lb/>
                    few days ago, directing my letter to my<lb/>
               <pb n="2" facs="Edgeworth_Geneve_33_2_1809_08_22_page02.jpg"/>
                    son <persName ref="./Personography.xml#EdgeH2">Henry</persName> in <placeName ref="./Placeography.xml#London_ENK">London</placeName> desiring that he would<lb/>
                    present or forward it by post to you <choice>
                  <orig>im=<lb/>
                        =mediately</orig>
                  <reg>immediately</reg>
               </choice>; but I fear, from your last<lb/>
                    just received, that mine will not reach<lb/>
                    you; therefore I write again to repeat t<lb/>he
                    purport of mine.<lb/>
            </p>
            <p>My son Henry is going to <choice>
                  <orig>Madei<lb/>
                    ra</orig>
                  <reg>
                     <placeName ref="./Placeography.xml#Madeira_PO">Madeira</placeName>
                  </reg>
               </choice>, where an English physician, as we are<lb/>
                    told, will have practice; he has good <choice>
                  <orig>recom-<lb/>
                        =mendations</orig>
                  <reg>recommendations</reg>
               </choice>, and will spend two or three<lb/>
                    years in that Island, and hopes to return<lb/>
                    with increased experience, and with the <choice>
                  <orig>repu-<lb/>
                        tation</orig>
                  <reg>
                     <hi rend="underline">reputation</hi>
                  </reg>
               </choice> of having been abroad, to settle in <choice>
                  <orig>&gt;Dub<lb/>
                            =lin</orig>
                  <reg>
                     <placeName ref="./Placeography.xml#Dublin_IE">Dublin</placeName>
                  </reg>
               </choice>. We hear that <persName ref="./Personography.xml#LansH1">Lord Lansdowne</persName> is going<lb/>
                    to <placeName ref="./Placeography.xml#Madeira_PO">Madeira</placeName>, - if my son's services during<lb/>
                    the voyage can be made acceptable to his<lb/>
                    Lordship it will be <del>an</del> advantageous -<lb/>
                    - I rely on your friendly recommendation<lb/>
            </p>
            <p/>
            <closer>
                    With true esteem &amp; regard I am<lb/>
                    My dear Sir<lb/>
                    Yours sincerely<lb/>
               <persName ref="./Personography.xml#EdgeR1">Rich<hi rend="superscript">r</hi> Lovell Edgeworth</persName>
               <lb/>
            </closer>
            <postscript>
               <p>perhaps we may meet in London next winter<lb/>
               </p>
               <p> Your writing is to us as legible as print<lb/>
                        - whether you write fast or with care Therefore<lb/>
                        do not trouble yourself <del>to write</del> about it.<lb/>
               </p>
            </postscript>
            <closer>
               <address>
                  <addrLine>To</addrLine>
                  <addrLine>
                     <persName ref="./Personography.xml#DumoE1">S. Dumont Esq<hi rend="superscript">r</hi>.</persName>
                  </addrLine>
               </address>
            </closer>
